dom-global-global.name: Global
dom-global-global.summary: A WebAssembly.Global() constructor creates a new Global object representing a global variable instance, accessible from both JavaScript and importable/exportable across one or more WebAssembly.Module instances. This allows dynamic linking of multiple modules.

chrome.notes: Constructing a Global with a value of v128 produces a TypeError.

deno.notes: Constructing a Global with a value of v128 produces a TypeError.

nodejs.notes: Constructing a Global with a value of v128 produces a TypeError.

edge_blink.notes: Constructing a Global with a value of v128 produces a TypeError.

dom-global-global.title: WebAssembly.Global() constructor

globals.name: Global
globals.summary: A WebAssembly.Global object represents a global variable instance, accessible from both JavaScript and importable/exportable across one or more WebAssembly.Module instances. This allows dynamic linking of multiple modules.
globals.title: WebAssembly.Global

dom-instance-instance.name: Instance
dom-instance-instance.summary: The WebAssembly.Instance() constructor creates a new Instance object which is a stateful, executable instance of a WebAssembly.Module.
dom-instance-instance.title: WebAssembly.Instance() constructor

dom-instance-exports.name: exports
dom-instance-exports.summary: The exports readonly property of the WebAssembly.Instance object prototype returns an object containing as its members all the functions exported from the WebAssembly module instance, to allow them to be accessed and used by JavaScript.
dom-instance-exports.title: WebAssembly.Instance.prototype.exports

instances.name: Instance
instances.summary: A WebAssembly.Instance object is a stateful, executable instance of a WebAssembly.Module. Instance objects contain all the Exported WebAssembly functions that allow calling into WebAssembly code from JavaScript.
instances.title: WebAssembly.Instance

exceptiondef-linkerror.name: LinkError
exceptiondef-linkerror.summary: The WebAssembly.LinkError() constructor creates a new WebAssembly LinkError object, which indicates an error during module instantiation (besides traps from the start function).
exceptiondef-linkerror.title: WebAssembly.LinkError() constructor

exceptiondef-linkerror.name: LinkError
exceptiondef-linkerror.summary: The WebAssembly.LinkError object indicates an error during module instantiation (besides traps from the start function).

dom-memory-memory.name: Memory
dom-memory-memory.summary: The WebAssembly.Memory() constructor creates a new Memory object whose buffer property is a resizable ArrayBuffer or SharedArrayBuffer that holds the raw bytes of memory accessed by a WebAssembly.Instance.
dom-memory-memory.title: WebAssembly.Memory() constructor

dom-memory-buffer.name: buffer
dom-memory-buffer.summary: The read-only buffer prototype property of the WebAssembly.Memory object returns the buffer contained in the memory. Depending on whether or not the memory was constructed with shared: true, the buffer is either an ArrayBuffer or a SharedArrayBuffer.
dom-memory-buffer.title: WebAssembly.Memory.prototype.buffer

dom-memory-grow.name: grow
dom-memory-grow.summary: The grow() prototype method of the WebAssembly.Memory object increases the size of the memory instance by a specified number of WebAssembly pages.
dom-memory-grow.title: WebAssembly.Memory.prototype.grow()

memories.name: Memory
memories.summary: The WebAssembly.Memory object is a resizable ArrayBuffer or SharedArrayBuffer that holds the raw bytes of memory accessed by a WebAssembly.Instance.
memories.title: WebAssembly.Memory

dom-module-module.name: Module
dom-module-module.summary: A WebAssembly.Module() constructor creates a new Module object containing stateless WebAssembly code that has already been compiled by the browser and can be efficiently shared with Workers, and instantiated multiple times.
dom-module-module.title: WebAssembly.Module() constructor

dom-module-customsections.name: customSections
dom-module-customsections.summary: The WebAssembly.customSections() function returns a copy of the contents of all custom sections in the given module with the given string name.
dom-module-customsections.title: WebAssembly.Module.customSections()

dom-module-exports.name: exports
dom-module-exports.summary: The WebAssembly.Module.exports() function returns an array containing descriptions of all the declared exports of the given Module.
dom-module-exports.title: WebAssembly.Module.exports()

dom-module-imports.name: imports
dom-module-imports.summary: The WebAssembly.imports() function returns an array containing descriptions of all the declared imports of the given Module.
dom-module-imports.title: WebAssembly.Module.imports()

modules.name: Module
modules.summary: A WebAssembly.Module object contains stateless WebAssembly code that has already been compiled by the browser — this can be efficiently shared with Workers, and instantiated multiple times.
modules.title: WebAssembly.Module

exceptiondef-runtimeerror.name: RuntimeError
exceptiondef-runtimeerror.summary: The WebAssembly.RuntimeError() constructor creates a new WebAssembly RuntimeError object — the type that is thrown whenever WebAssembly specifies a trap.
exceptiondef-runtimeerror.title: WebAssembly.RuntimeError() constructor

exceptiondef-runtimeerror.name: RuntimeError
exceptiondef-runtimeerror.summary: The WebAssembly.RuntimeError object is the error type that is thrown whenever WebAssembly specifies a trap.
exceptiondef-runtimeerror.title: WebAssembly.RuntimeError

dom-table-table.name: Table
dom-table-table.summary: The WebAssembly.Table() constructor creates a new Table object of the given size and element type.
dom-table-table.title: WebAssembly.Table() constructor

dom-table-get.name: get
dom-table-get.summary: The get() prototype method of the WebAssembly.Table() object retrieves a function reference stored at a given index.
dom-table-get.title: WebAssembly.Table.prototype.get()

dom-table-grow.name: grow
dom-table-grow.summary: The grow() prototype method of the WebAssembly.Table object increases the size of the Table instance by a specified number of elements.
dom-table-grow.title: WebAssembly.Table.prototype.grow()

dom-table-length.name: length
dom-table-length.summary: The read-only length prototype property of the WebAssembly.Table object returns the length of the table, i.e. the number of elements in the table.
dom-table-length.title: WebAssembly.Table.prototype.length

dom-table-set.name: set
dom-table-set.summary: The set() prototype method of the WebAssembly.Table object mutates a reference stored at a given index to a different value.
dom-table-set.title: WebAssembly.Table.prototype.set()

tables.name: Table
tables.summary: The WebAssembly.Table() object is a JavaScript wrapper object — an array-like structure representing a WebAssembly Table, which stores function references. A table created by JavaScript or in WebAssembly code will be accessible and mutable from both JavaScript and WebAssembly.
tables.title: WebAssembly.Table

dom-webassembly-compile.name: compile
dom-webassembly-compile.summary: The WebAssembly.compile() function compiles WebAssembly binary code into a WebAssembly.Module object. This function is useful if it is necessary to compile a module before it can be instantiated (otherwise, the WebAssembly.instantiate() function should be used).
dom-webassembly-compile.title: WebAssembly.compile()

dom-webassembly-instantiate.name: instantiate
dom-webassembly-instantiate.summary: The WebAssembly.instantiate() function allows you to compile and instantiate WebAssembly code. This function has two overloads:
dom-webassembly-instantiate.title: WebAssembly.instantiate()

dom-webassembly-validate.name: validate
dom-webassembly-validate.summary: The WebAssembly.validate() function validates a given typed array of WebAssembly binary code, returning whether the bytes form a valid Wasm module (true) or not (false).
dom-webassembly-validate.title: WebAssembly.validate()

webassembly-namespace.name: WebAssembly
webassembly-namespace.summary: The WebAssembly JavaScript object acts as the namespace for all WebAssembly-related functionality.
webassembly-namespace.title: WebAssembly
